#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
Genesi AI Daemon (genesi-aid) — adaptive local-AI optimizer.

Profiles the host once, then while an AI inference process runs it applies only
the optimizations that THIS machine can benefit from (CPU governor, memory, GPU
clocks/power, platform power profile, process priority). Every change is
captured before it's touched and restored when the workload stops — and the
snapshot lives in /run so even a daemon restart restores cleanly.

IPC (so the daemon can keep PrivateTmp hardening):
    /run/genesi-ai-mode/force      "on" | "off" | absent(=auto)   (user-written)
    /run/genesi-ai-mode/state.json daemon status (widget / CLI read this)
    /run/genesi-aid-originals.json  pre-change snapshot, root-only (0600)
"""

